<subSubSection id="C367656E7902FFA243429CC0D4DBFD27" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC236E57902FFA343429CC0D3C4FA12" blockId="10.[491,1559,1183,1484]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">
Diagnosis — SIF = 6B-B-3-2111.0000; fsp = 7.7.7; fCx = 1.1.1; fSt = 2.2; fPp = B/B/BBB; fSc: AL&gt;= PL 
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA343CD9C9CD595FB61" box="[668,695,1219,1242]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">≫</emphasis>
AM. Cheliceral blade with tricuspid cap; galeal setae branched; palpal claw with 3 prongs; palpal femoral, genual, and tibial setae branched; palpal tarsus with 6 branched setae and basal tarsala. Scutum nearly pentagonal, wider than long, with broadly rounded posterior margin, bearing 1 anteromedian, 2 anterolateral and 2 posterolateral scutal setae; anterolateral scutal setae longest; sensilla globose, sensillary bases posterior to level of PLs; eyes 2 + 2. Legs 7-segmented, with 1 pair of claws and claw-like empodium; tibialae II situated in distal half of segment, not in tandem; mastisetae absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236E57902FFA343429DEBD32FFA77" blockId="10.[491,1559,1183,1484]" box="[531,1037,1459,1484]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">
<typeStatus id="54C688477902FFA343429DEBD56AFA77" box="[531,584,1460,1484]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Type</typeStatus>
species — 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA343929DECD4EBFA70" authority="Stekolnikov, 2018" authorityName="Stekolnikov" authorityYear="2018" box="[707,969,1459,1483]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Makwacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrodromi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA343929DECD4EBFA70" box="[707,969,1459,1483]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Makwacarus petrodromi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA3429E9DEBD32FFA77" bold="true" box="[975,1037,1460,1484]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23A578C7902FFA3429E9DEBD32FFA77" box="[975,1037,1460,1484]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236E57902FFA343429DA6D5A4F988" blockId="10.[491,1436,1529,1587]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">
Host — four-toed elephant shrew (
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA342F89DA6D377F9AA" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1956" box="[937,1109,1529,1553]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macroscelidea" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Macroscelidea</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA345389DA6D232F9AA" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1838" box="[1129,1296,1529,1553]" class="Mammalia" family="Macroscelididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macroscelidea" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Macroscelididae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA344429DA6D554F988" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1846" class="Mammalia" family="Macroscelididae" genus="Petrodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macroscelidea" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tetradactylus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA344429DA6D554F988" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Petrodromus tetradactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236E57902FFA343429E3FD350F920" blockId="10.[491,1510,1632,1691]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">
Etymology — The name of the new genus is combined from the name of 
<typeStatus id="54C688477902FFA344319E3ED2ACF9C2" box="[1376,1422,1633,1657]" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">type</typeStatus>
locality (Makwa) and the new Latin word acarus meaning “mite”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236E57902FFA243429E97D273FE9B" blockId="10.[491,1506,1736,2002]" lastBlockId="11.[491,1577,229,668]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">
Differential diagnosis — By the shape of scutum with broadly rounded, protruded margin, globose sensilla, and by the relation between lengths of scutal setae (AL&gt;= 
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA344F89EB4D2E6F8B9" box="[1449,1476,1771,1794]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">≫</emphasis>
PL AM), the new genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA3420D9F52D37DF89E" authority="Audy, 1954" authorityName="Audy" authorityYear="1954" box="[860,1119,1805,1829]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Helenicula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA3420D9F52D4F3F89E" box="[860,977,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Helenicula</emphasis>
Audy, 1954
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA345369F52D299F89E" authority="Oudemans, 1910" authorityName="Oudemans" authorityYear="1910" box="[1127,1467,1805,1829]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Schoengastia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA345369F52D3DAF89E" box="[1127,1272,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Schoengastia</emphasis>
Oudemans, 1910
</taxonomicName>
, some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA343CD9F6FD233F8FC" authority="Vercammen-Grandjean, 1960" authorityName="Vercammen-Grandjean" authorityYear="1960" box="[668,1297,1839,1863]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Herpetacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Abonnencia">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA343CD9F6FD4EBF8FC" box="[668,969,1839,1863]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Herpetacarus (Abonnencia)</emphasis>
Vercammen-Grandjean, 1960
</taxonomicName>
, and some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA343589F0DD371F8D1" authority="Vercammen-Grandjean, 1967" authorityName="Vercammen-Grandjean" authorityYear="1967" box="[521,1107,1874,1898]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Guntheria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Phyllacarus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA343589F0DD42DF8D1" box="[521,783,1874,1898]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Guntheria (Phyllacarus)</emphasis>
Vercammen-Grandjean, 1967
</taxonomicName>
, first of all, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA345859F0DD407F837" authority="(Womersley et Heaslip, 1943)" authorityName="Womersley" authorityYear="1939" baseAuthorityName="Womersley et Heaslip" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Guntheria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="innisfailensis">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA345859F0DD2F6F8D1" box="[1236,1492,1874,1898]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Guntheria innisfailensis</emphasis>
(Womersley et Heaslip, 1943)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36A76757902FFA3423A9F2BD4F2F837" box="[875,976,1908,1932]" name="Australia" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Australia</collectingCountry>
. The position of tibialae II in distal half of segment and not in tandem is one more trait common for the new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA3445E9FC8D2A6F814" authorityName="Audy" authorityYear="1954" box="[1295,1412,1943,1967]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Helenicula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA3445E9FC8D2A6F814" box="[1295,1412,1943,1967]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Helenicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667902FFA340BA9FE5D332F869" authority="Vercammen-Grandjean, 1971" authorityName="Vercammen-Grandjean" authorityYear="1971" box="[491,1040,1978,2002]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Schoengastia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equina">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77902FFA340BA9FE5D5EFF869" box="[491,717,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="274">Schoengastia equina</emphasis>
Vercammen-Grandjean, 1971
</taxonomicName>
. The relation of lengths of leg tarsalae with tarsala II longer than tarsala I and the position of tarsala I distal to microtarsala are also characteristic for the new genus and for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667903FFA242C69957D26FFE9B" authority="(Nadchatram &amp; Traub 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Nadchatram &amp; Traub" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[919,1357,264,288]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Helenicula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77903FFA242C69957D32EFE9B" box="[919,1036,264,288]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">Helenicula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B147903FFA245489957D264FE9B" author="Nadchatram M. &amp; Traub R." box="[1049,1350,264,288]" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" pagination="562 - 597" refId="ref11869" refString="Nadchatram M., Traub R. 1971. Chiggers of the genus Helenicula of the Old World including descriptions of 9 new species (Acarina: Prostigmata, Trombiculidae). Journal of Medical Entomology, 8: 562 - 597. doi: 10.1093 / jmedent / 8.5.562" type="journal article" year="1971">Nadchatram &amp; Traub 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236E57903FFA243429974D4DBFD27" blockId="11.[491,1577,229,668]" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">
The new genus, however, differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667903FFA242E99974D30FFEF8" baseAuthorityName="Nadchatram &amp; Traub" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[952,1069,299,323]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Helenicula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77903FFA242E99974D30FFEF8" box="[952,1069,299,323]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">Helenicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the presence of six setae on palpal tarsus vs. 4-5 and in the sensillary bases situated far apart (distance between sensillary bases is roughly equal to the distance between a sensillary base and a base of posterolateral seta) vs. situated close together (with the gap being less than the diameter of either base). The new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667903FFA2432599EAD427FE76" authorityName="Oudemans" authorityYear="1910" box="[628,773,437,461]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Schoengastia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77903FFA2432599EAD427FE76" box="[628,773,437,461]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">Schoengastia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having cheliceral blade with usual tricuspid cap only, without longitudinal row of teeth, in the palpal tarsus 6B vs. 7BS, and in having branched galeal setae vs. always nude. The new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667903FFA242B299A4D233FDA9" authority="" authorityName="Vercammen-Grandjean" authorityYear="1960" box="[995,1297,506,530]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Herpetacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Abonnencia">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77903FFA242B299A4D233FDA9" box="[995,1297,506,530]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">Herpetacarus (Abonnencia)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having palpal tarsus 6B vs. 7B, galeal setae branched vs. nude and scutum not telostigmal (sensillary bases are not significantly closer to the bases of posterolateral setae than to each other). The new genus differs from a very speciose and heterogeneous subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667903FFA245C39A3ED2B5FDC2" authority="" authorityName="Vercammen-Grandjean" authorityYear="1967" box="[1170,1431,609,633]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Guntheria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Phyllacarus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77903FFA245C39A3ED2B5FDC2" box="[1170,1431,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">Guntheria (Phyllacarus)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the palpal tarsus 6B vs. 5B (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B147903FFA243A29ADBD4CCFD27" author="Domrow R. &amp; Lester L. N." box="[755,1006,644,668]" pageId="11" pageNumber="275" refId="ref11498" refString="Domrow R., Lester L. N. 1985. Chiggers of Australia (Acari: Trombiculidae): an annotated checklist," type="book" year="1985">
Domrow &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F8077903FFA242249ADAD495FD27" box="[885,951,645,668]" country="United Kingdom" name="Leicester" pageId="11" pageNumber="275">Lester</collectingRegion>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
